-- Vestas’s Chief Says 2012 Will Be a ‘Very, Very’ Busy Year
-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 2012-02-08T09:29:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/vestas-s-chief-says-2012-will-be-a-very-very-busy-year.html
  Vestas Wind Systems A/S (VWS)  Chief
Executive Officer  Ditlev Engel  said he expects 2012 to be a
“very, very busy year” for the world’s largest wind turbine
maker, with activity levels 40 percent higher than last year.
Engel spoke in a Bloomberg television interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
